{"id": "EUVD-2025-14104", "enisaUuid": "b7006c4b-5dd7-3e03-93d2-d0dd851339d7", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\npds_core: make wait_context part of q_info\n\nMake the wait_context a full part of the q_info struct rather\nthan a stack variable that goes away after pdsc_adminq_post()\nis done so that the context is still available after the wait\nloop has given up.\n\nThere was a case where a slow development firmware caused\nthe adminq request to time out, but then later the FW finally\nfinished the request and sent the interrupt.  The handler tried\nto complete_all() the completion context that had been created\non the stack in pdsc_adminq_post() but no longer existed.\nThis caused bad pointer usage, kernel crashes, and much wailing\nand gnashing of teeth.", "datePublished": "2025-05-09T09:33:20", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-12T21:31:03", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1d7c4b2b0bbfb09b55b2dc0e2355d7936bf89381", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/66d7702b42ffdf0dce4808626088268a4e905ca6", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/520f012fe75fb8efc9f16a57ef929a7a2115d892", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3f77c3dfffc7063428b100c4945ca2a7a8680380", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-37886"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-37886"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "124a8793-297c-3428-8920-1fcfd41bddcf", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "01ba61b55b2041a39c54aefb3153c770dd59a0ef <520f012fe75fb8efc9f16a57ef929a7a2115d892"}, {"id": "161e6a4b-341a-3932-ab02-c419b1509910", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "01ba61b55b2041a39c54aefb3153c770dd59a0ef <1d7c4b2b0bbfb09b55b2dc0e2355d7936bf89381"}, {"id": "2de1932b-0295-3c4c-88c3-43d7cc4be4ae", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "01ba61b55b2041a39c54aefb3153c770dd59a0ef <66d7702b42ffdf0dce4808626088268a4e905ca6"}, {"id": "2dff4a9f-6db4-3099-b0f5-7145a78e73d5", "product": {"name": "Linux"},